                                <condition>A fine-grained micaceous sandstone slab with some flaking (including loss of at least one ogham character) and damage to the lower left, narrow face. Widest at the top, tapering downwards <q>to a point</q>, according to Macalister (1945, 134), but the bottom of the stone is now mounted in a stand and so not accessible. Macalister dismisses the inscription <q>on account of its orthographical eccentricities, and the unlikeness of the stone to anything which an ogham carver would naturally choose</q> and doesn't give it a CIIC number.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
